To visualize how these signals are routed, use the Chip Planner task "Report Clock Details".
To manually specify the size and placement of these signals, use the Assignment Editor to make Clock Region assignments.


+-----------------------------------+
; Non-Global High Fan-Out Signals   ;
+------+---------+------------------+
; Name ; Fan-Out ; Physical Fan-Out ;
+------+---------+------------------+
; ar   ; 1141    ; 113              ;
; ~GND ; 736     ; 20               ;
+------+---------+------------------+
Fan-Out is the number of connections the specified signal drives on the netlist.
Physical Fan-Out is the number of connections needed to route the signal, which may be lower if multiple netlist destinations share the same routing port.


